=============================================
Battleship
	by Clifton Thomas

=============================================
Institution: Georgia Institute of Technology
Class: ECE2035
Project: Battleship
---------------------------------------------


---------------------------------------------
Pre-requisites:

-install pySerial python module on host pc

-construct circuit as outlined in 'BattleshipPinout.pdf'

-place 'bomb.wav' file inside '/wavfiles' directory on microSD card

-unzip 'Battleship_MbedFiles.zip' and compile its components in mbed cloud compiler

-flash binaries to mbed
----------------------------------------------


----------------------------------------------
Usage:

-ON HOST PC: execute python script as 'python battleship.py' from terminal

-ON MBED: use reset button to run the program binary
----------------------------------------------


----------------------------------------------
Misc:
-to find which com port the serial device is linked to, type the following at the terminal:
	LINUX:   'ls /dev/ttyACM*'
	MAC OSX: 'ls /dev/tty.usbmodem*'
==============================================
END
